England World Cup winner Jason Robinson has revealed he once contemplated suicide during a troubled period of his career in which he was arrested for violent offences .
Speaking in the documentary Jason Robinson : Sports Life Stories will be broadcast on ITV4 at 10 pm on Tuesday , the 40-year-old former dual-code international admitted he had been a heavy drinker during his early days at rugby league club Wigan .
Robinson scored for England in the 2003 World Cup final victory against Australia .